            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is the BlockFi Interest Account (BIA)?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "The BIA is an interest-bearing account, which provides market-leading yields to crypto investors who store their Bitcoin, Ether, and Gemini Dollar (GUSD) at BlockFi."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How does the BlockFi Interest Account (BIA) work?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "BlockFi clients can securely store their Bitcoin, Ether,and Gemini Dollar (GUSD) at BlockFi and receive interest paid monthly in cryptocurrency."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How and how often is interest paid out?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "The interest earned in your BIA will be paid out at the beginning of every month. BIA account holders will be able to access a history of their interest payments and view their total balance on their BlockFi dashboard. Interest is paid in the client’s deposited currency, meaning Bitcoin will earn Bitcoin, Ether will earn Ether."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Does Interest in a BIA Compound?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Yes, interest earned in the BIA compounds monthly. This means that if you earn interest in Month 1, your next interest payment will be calculated off of your new total balance (old balance + interest payment from Month 1). Learn more about how compound interest works."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Does BlockFi have 2FA?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Yes! Two - factor authentication (2 FA) is the industry standard for securing your online accounts. Once enabled, 2 FA adds a second layer of protection to your BlockFi account. When you login, you’ll be prompted to input your password and a verification code generated by authenticator app. You can setup 2 FA on your BlockFi account using the Google Authenticator app, available on Android and iOS mobile devices. Once enabled, you will only be able to log in to your BlockFi account with a code generated by the app. This code regenerates every 30 seconds. As a precaution, BlockFi strongly recommends that clients write down and store their authenticator token code in a safe and accessible place. We urge all account holders to enable 2 FA on their accounts. While we strive to ensure that no unwanted activity occurs, BlockFi is not responsible for any unauthorized users that may access your account."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How do I enable 2FA on my BlockFi account?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "To enable 2 FA on your BlockFi account, login to the client dashboard, click on your name at the top right of the screen, and select ‘Settings’. Next, click the “Account & Settings” tab and navigate to the “Two - Factor Authentication” section. Click the “Enable 2 FA” button to get started. Follow the step - by - step instructions to complete the process. Using the Google Authenticator app, please scan the following QR code or manually input the authenticator token code. For your security."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How can I withdraw my funds from a BIA?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Sign in to your dashboard, select the asset you wish to withdraw, click on the withdraw button, enter the amount you wish to withdraw and the wallet address for return. Your withdrawal request should be processed within one business day of the request."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Who is eligible for the BlockFi Interest Account?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "The BlockFi Interest Account is available to clients worldwide, with a few exceptions. For example, due to legal restrictions, BIA is not available to users located in sanctioned or watchlist countries. Additionally, the Interest Account services clients in most U.S. states, but is not available New York, Connecticut, Washington, and Wyoming."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Can collateral posted for a loan be used to earn interest?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Collateral posted for a loan is not eligible for earning interest."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What does BlockFi do with account assets?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "BlockFi generates interest on assets held in Interest Accounts by lending them to trusted institutional and corporate borrowers. To ensure loan performance, BlockFi lends crypto on over - collateralized terms (similar to the structure of our crypto - backed loans). Furthermore, BlockFi’s automated risk management system monitors positions 24/7, providing the same trusted risk management system used with BlockFi’s crypto-backed loans. BlockFi has the ability to terminate a borrow in a timely fashion and also manages reserve balances to facilitate clients withdrawals from Interest Accounts. Reserves are stored securely with Gemini, a New York trust company regulated by NYDFS. Learn more about how BlockFi stores clients assets."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What are the tax implications of the BlockFi Interest Account?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "US clients will receive a 1099 shortly after the end of the year which details the total dollar value of interest paid over the year. Clients can provide this information to their tax preparers who can advise based on individual facts and circumstances. International clients are responsible for determining their own tax obligations. BlockFi will provide international clients with a summary of their account activity upon request."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Can I send BlockFi ETH through a smart contract?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "ETH sent to BlockFi through a smart contracts will show up on users dashboards,but there may be delays arising from special transaction requirements in the contract.For the fastest credit, we recommend sending ETH normally."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What are the risks associated with a BlockFi Interest Account?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "BlockFi client funds are structured to be at the top of the capital stack, senior to BlockFi equity and BlockFi employee capital. This means BlockFi’s business and client incentives are aligned and BlockFi would take a loss before any client would. BlockFi implements very thoughtful risk management practices and technology to mitigate the risk, but you should not view the BlockFi Interest Account as a savings account or brokerage account with FDIC or SIPC insurance."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is Interest Payment Flex?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Interest Payment Flex allows BIA clients to choose the currency their interest is paid in. For example, if you currently have a BTC interest account with BlockFi, you can choose to receive interest in any of the offered currencies."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How do I enable Interest Payment Flex?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Clients can enable this feature by navigating to the Settings page of their account and visiting the “Interest Preferences” tab. There, you’ll be able to choose to receive interest payments in one of the available currencies."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How does Interest Payment Flex work?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "At the end of each month, our system checks if a client has opted into this feature. If so, all accrued interest will be paid in the selected currency. Our system will perform this calculation based on market prices at the time of the interest payment. All accrued interest will then be displayed as a single payment transaction within the BlockFi dashboard."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What fees are associated with Interest Payment Flex?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "If you elect for interest to be paid in a cryptocurrency that is different from the cryptocurrency on which the interest has been earned, BlockFi may charge an administrative fee of up to 1% of the total amount of interest accrued for the month, depending on the cryptocurrency selected and market conditions at the time of the payment."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How did you determine the loan to value ratio?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "We have performed extensive risk modeling and determined that our LTVs were sufficiently conservative — in order to have a limited number of expected trigger events and provide our clients with breathing room in the event of market volatility. The LTV ratios protect you and us.Learn more about how LTVs work."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Is there a prepayment penalty?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "There is no penalty for early repayment, so if you payoff early the remaining interest is forgiven. Once your loan is paid off, collateral is released to your preferred address. Learn more about how prepayment works."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What happens if the value of my cryptoassets significantly increase or decrease during the one year term",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "If the value of your coins significantly increase then they are kept in storage until the loan is paid. If your coins significantly decrease then that sets off a trigger event, and you will have to add more collateral to your account to maintain a minimum LTV ratio. You can use the value of your cryptoassets stored with BlockFi to make principal and interest payments at anytime. We plan to add the ability to draw more USD funds in the event of price appreciation over time. Learn more about what happens to your collateral with price fluctuations."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How can I get a BlockFi loan?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Create an account, click on the Loan tab, click Apply and fill out the application, you will receive a decision from our team in less than 24 hours, review your loan offer and sign the loan agreement."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Will my credit score be affected by applying for a BlockFi loan?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "No, BlockFi does not do a hard or soft pull on your credit score so there is no impact for applying."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Where can I login to view my BlockFi loan details?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Your loan details are viewable from within our client portal. Login to your account. Additional information can be viewed at our loan servicer, who will reach out to you via email post-funding to set up an account. You will be able to view your loan details, collateral amount, and set up auto-pay."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How do I payoff my BlockFi loan?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "When it is time to payoff your loan, BlockFi offers flexibility to meet your specific timing and financing needs. To access this information at any time, please go to our resource center and select the “Paying off your BlockFi Loan” article."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Where are my cryptoassets stored?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Your cryptoassets are stored with a depository trust and licensed custodian, Gemini. The majority of assets stored with Gemini are held in cold storage."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is BlockFi?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "BlockFi offers financial products designed to help cryptocurrency holders to do more with their digital assets. The company currently services clients worldwide, including 47 U.S. states, with interest earning accounts and low cost USD loans backed by crypto. BlockFi is the only independent lender with institutional backing from investors that include Galaxy Digital, Susquehanna, Akuna Capital, Fidelity, Recruit Strategic Partners, ConsenSys Ventures, SoFi, Coinbase Ventures, CMT Digital and Morgan Creek Digital."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What are the benefits of using BlockFi’s services?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "BlockFi offers institutional - quality financial services to crypto investors. Everything from our client services to our products are based on tried and tested policies to provide a superior experience for our clients. The BlockFi Interest Account provides clients with the ability to earn more crypto while holding for long - term investments. Interest is paid monthly and compounds. This significantly increases the potential earnings of long - term account holders."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Why BlockFi?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "We offer the best rates, most flexible structures and highest degree of security available in the blockchain lending ecosystem. Additionally, we operate within regulatory guidelines at the federal and state level in the United States. The BlockFi team has decades of experience in consumer lending and financial services. We are the only independent lender with institutional backing from investors that include Galaxy Digital, Susquehanna, Akuna Capital, Fidelity, Recruit Strategic Partners, ConsenSys Ventures, SoFi, Coinbase Ventures, CMT Digital and Morgan Creek Digital. Learn more about our investors."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Who can use BlockFi?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "BlockFi services individuals and businesses worldwide, including 47 U.S. states, which is the largest footprint in the industry."
            }
        }]
