		j$('#header_container').addClass('white_header');</script> <style type="text/css">.page_title_ctn{padding-top:50px;padding-bottom:50px}</style><style type="text/css">.page_title_ctn{background:url(https://blockfi.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/resources-background.svg) top center;background-size:cover;border-bottom:1px solid #ecf0f1}</style><div class="section def_section"><div class="wrapper section_wrapper"><div id="fw_c" class="clearfix tf_single_page"><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid  " style="padding-top: 100px;"><div class="vc_span4 wpb_column vc_column_container "><div class="vc_column-inner "><div class="wpb_wrapper"><div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element   ct_qic9g728hxsuhm44702c"><div class="wpb_wrapper"><div id="faq-nav" class="sticky" style="top: 180px;"><div class="faq-nav-inner"><h4 id="link-heading-loan-structure" data-scrollto="interest-ccount">BlockFi Interest Account</h4><ul><li style="list-style-type: none;"><ul><li data-scrollto="faq-a-what">What is the BlockFi Interest Account (BIA)?</li><li data-scrollto="faq-a-how">How does the BlockFi Interest Account (BIA) work?</li><li data-scrollto="faq-a-often-paid">How and how often is interest paid out?</li><li data-scrollto="faq-a-compound">Does Interest in a BIA Compound?</li><li data-scrollto="faq-a-minmax">What are the minimums and maximums for the BIA?</li><li data-scrollto="faq-a-2FA">Does BlockFi have 2FA?</li><li data-scrollto="faq-a-enable">How do I enable 2FA on my BlockFi account?</li><li data-scrollto="faq-a-wallet">Does BlockFi have a Wallet Address Book and Whitelisting?</li><li data-scrollto="faq-a-withdraw">How can I withdraw my funds from a BIA?</li><li data-scrollto="faq-a-eligible">Who is eligible for the BlockFi Interest Account?</li><li data-scrollto="faq-a-collateral">Can collateral posted for a loan be used to earn interest?</li><li data-scrollto="faq-a-assets">What does BlockFi do with account assets?</li><li data-scrollto="faq-a-tax">What are the tax implications of the BlockFi Interest Account?</li><li data-scrollto="faq-a-smart-contract">Can I send BlockFi ETH through a smart contract?</li><li data-scrollto="faq-a-fees">Does the BlockFi Interest Account have withdrawal fees?</li><li data-scrollto="faq-a-risks">What are the risks associated with a BlockFi Interest Account?</li></ul></li></ul><h4 id="link-heading-loan-structure" data-scrollto="heading-loan-structure">BlockFi Loan Structure</h4><ul><li style="list-style-type: none;"><ul><li id="link-faq-a" class="" data-scrollto="faq-a">How did you determine the loan to value ratio?</li><li id="link-faq-b" class="" data-scrollto="faq-b">Is there a prepayment penalty?</li><li id="link-faq-c" class="" data-scrollto="faq-c">What happens if the value of my cryptoassets significantly increase or decrease during the one year term?</li><li id="link-faq-d" class="" data-scrollto="faq-d">What is a trigger event?</li><li id="link-faq-e" class="" data-scrollto="faq-e">How will I know if I am close to a trigger event?</li></ul></li></ul><h4 id="link-heading-loan-process" data-scrollto="heading-loan-process">Loan Process</h4><ul><li style="list-style-type: none;"><ul><li id="link-faq-l" class="" data-scrollto="faq-l">How can I get a loan?</li><li id="link-faq-m" class="" data-scrollto="faq-m">Will my credit score be affected by applying for a BlockFi loan?</li><li id="link-faq-n" class="" data-scrollto="faq-n">Where can I login to view my loan details?</li></ul></li></ul><h4 id="link-heading-rates" data-scrollto="heading-rates">Rates</h4><ul><li style="list-style-type: none;"><ul><li id="link-faq-f" class="" data-scrollto="faq-f">What is the interest rate?</li></ul></li></ul><h4 id="link-heading-security-storage" data-scrollto="heading-security-storage">Security and Storage</h4><ul><li style="list-style-type: none;"><ul><li id="link-faq-g" class="" data-scrollto="faq-g">Where are my cryptoassets stored?</li></ul></li></ul><h4 id="link-heading-general" data-scrollto="heading-general">General</h4><ul><li style="list-style-type: none;"><ul><li id="link-faq-h" class="" data-scrollto="faq-h">What is BlockFi?</li><li id="link-faq-i" class="" data-scrollto="faq-i">What are the benefits of using BlockFi’s product?</li><li id="link-faq-j" class="active" data-scrollto="faq-j">Why BlockFi?</li><li id="link-faq-k" class="" data-scrollto="faq-k">Who can use the product?</li><li data-scrollto="faq-z">How does the refer a friend program work?</li></ul></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="vc_span8 wpb_column vc_column_container "><div class="vc_column-inner "><div class="wpb_wrapper"><div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element   ct_i4amohsmc19nr7x15cnc"><div class="wpb_wrapper"><h2 id="interest-ccount">BlockFi Interest Account</h2><div class="row faq-item"><div id="contactinfo" class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"><h3 id="faq-a-what">What is the BlockFi Interest Account (BIA)?</h3><div class="answer"><p>The BIA is an interest-bearing account, which provides market-leading yields to crypto investors who store their crypto at BlockFi.</p><h3 id="faq-a-how">How does the BlockFi Interest Account (BIA) work?</h3><div class="answer"><p>BlockFi clients can securely store the crypto of their choosing at BlockFi and receive interest paid monthly in cryptocurrency. <a href="https://blockfi.com/earn-bitcoin-interest/">Learn more about how the BlockFi Interest Account works</a>.</p><h3 id="faq-a-often-paid">How and how often is interest paid out?</h3><div class="answer"><p>The interest earned in your BIA will be paid out at the beginning of every month. BIA account holders will be able to access a history of their interest payments and view their total balance on their BlockFi dashboard. Interest is paid in the client’s deposited currency, meaning Bitcoin will earn Bitcoin and Ether will earn Ether. If you would like to be paid out in a different currency than the one you deposited, you can use Interest Payment Flex.</p><h3 id="faq-a-compound">Does Interest in a BIA Compound?</h3><div class="answer"><p>Yes, interest earned in the BIA compounds monthly. This means that if you earn interest in Month 1, your next interest payment will be calculated off of your new total balance (old balance + interest payment from Month 1). Learn more about <a href="https://blockfi.com/earn-crypto/">how compound interest works</a>.</p><h3 id="faq-a-minmax">What are the minimums and maximums for the BIA?</h3><div class="answer"><p>There is no minimum or maximum deposit for the BlockFi Interest Account. To learn more about BlockFi rates and interest tiers, visit the <a href="https://blockfi.com/rates/">rates page</a>.</p><div class="answer"><h3 id="faq-a-2FA">Does BlockFi have 2FA?</h3><div class="answer"><p>Yes! <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Two-factor_authentication">Two-factor authentication</a> (2FA) is the industry standard for securing your online accounts. Once enabled, 2FA adds a second layer of protection to your BlockFi account. When you login, you’ll be prompted to input your password and a verification code generated by authenticator app.<br> You can setup 2FA on your BlockFi account using the <a href="https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/1066447">Google Authenticator</a> app, available on <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.google.android.apps.authenticator2&amp;hl=en_US">Android</a> and <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/google-authenticator/id388497605?mt=8">iOS</a> mobile devices. Once enabled, you will only be able to log in to your BlockFi account with a code generated by the app. This code regenerates every 30 seconds. As a precaution, BlockFi strongly recommends that clients write down and store their authenticator token code in a safe and accessible place.<br> We urge all account holders to enable 2FA on their accounts. While we strive to ensure that no unwanted activity occurs, BlockFi is not responsible for any unauthorized users that may access your account.</p><h3 id="faq-a-enable">How do I enable 2FA on my BlockFi account?</h3><div class="answer"><p><img class="wp-image-2560 alignright lazyloaded" src="./FAQ.blade_files/2fadashboard.png" data-lazy-src="https://blockfi.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/2fadashboard.png" alt="" width="284" height="146" data-lazy-srcset="https://blockfi.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/2fadashboard.png 838w, https://blockfi.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/2fadashboard-300x154.png 300w, https://blockfi.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/2fadashboard-768x394.png 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 284px) 100vw, 284px" sizes="(max-width: 284px) 100vw, 284px" srcset="https://blockfi.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/2fadashboard.png 838w, https://blockfi.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/2fadashboard-300x154.png 300w, https://blockfi.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/2fadashboard-768x394.png 768w" data-was-processed="true"><noscript><img class="wp-image-2560 alignright" src="https://blockfi.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/2fadashboard.png" alt="" width="284" height="146" srcset="https://blockfi.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/2fadashboard.png 838w, https://blockfi.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/2fadashboard-300x154.png 300w, https://blockfi.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/2fadashboard-768x394.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 284px) 100vw, 284px" /></noscript>To enable 2FA on your BlockFi account, login to the client dashboard, click on your name at the top right of the screen, and select ‘Settings’. Next, click the “Account &amp; Settings” tab and navigate to the “Two-Factor Authentication” section. Click the “Enable 2FA” button to get started. Follow the step-by-step instructions to complete the process.</p><ol><li>Using the <a href="https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/1066447">Google Authenticator app</a>, please scan the following QR code or manually input the authenticator token code.</li><li>For your security, BlockFi strongly urges that you write down your auth token and store it in a safe place. If you lose access to your account or get a new phone, this token will help you regain access to your BlockFi account.</li><li>Once it’s written down, click the “I Saved My Auth Token” button. A 6-digit input field will appear below the button.</li><li>Google Authenticator will generate a 6-digit BlockFi verification code. A new code will generate every 30 seconds.</li><li>Input the BlockFi verification code from the authenticator app into the “Enter Google 2FA Code” field.</li></ol><h3 id="faq-a-wallet">Does BlockFi have a Wallet Address Book and Whitelisting?</h3><div class="answer"><p>Yes. We offer a Wallet Address Book that provides BlockFi clients the opportunity to pre-select and save your frequently used crypto wallet addresses. We also offer Whitelisting, which adds another layer of security to your BlockFi account. Learn how to use these settings <a href="https://blockfi.com/whitelist-crypto-wallet-addresses/">here</a>.</p></div><h3 id="faq-a-withdraw">How can I withdraw my funds from a BIA?</h3><div class="answer"><div><img class="wp-image-5420 alignright lazyloaded" src="./FAQ.blade_files/blockfi_withdrawal.png" data-lazy-src="https://blockfi.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/blockfi_withdrawal.png" alt="" width="369" height="259" data-lazy-srcset="https://blockfi.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/blockfi_withdrawal.png 587w, https://blockfi.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/blockfi_withdrawal-300x211.png 300w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 369px) 100vw, 369px" sizes="(max-width: 369px) 100vw, 369px" srcset="https://blockfi.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/blockfi_withdrawal.png 587w, https://blockfi.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/blockfi_withdrawal-300x211.png 300w" data-was-processed="true"><noscript><img class="wp-image-5420 alignright" src="https://blockfi.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/blockfi_withdrawal.png" alt="" width="369" height="259" srcset="https://blockfi.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/blockfi_withdrawal.png 587w, https://blockfi.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/blockfi_withdrawal-300x211.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 369px) 100vw, 369px" /></noscript>Please follow the instructions below to initiate a withdrawal:</div><div></div><div><ol><li><a href="https://blockfi.com/signin" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://blockfi.com/signin&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1560438864854000&amp;usg=AFQjCNHzZ4wBj9vF0wUTurw0G2lqd5lM7w">Sign in</a>&nbsp;to your dashboard</li><li>Click on the “Interest Account” tab</li><li>Select the asset you wish to withdraw</li><li>Click on the “Withdraw” button (image below)</li><li>Enter the amount you wish to withdraw and the wallet address for return</li></ol><p>Withdrawals are processed one business day after a 24 hour security hold. All withdrawals are processed by 8:00 PM EST on weekdays, subject to additional review from our compliance team.</p><p>Please note that by confirming your wallet address above, you are authorizing BlockFi to return the requested collateral amount to the wallet address provided. BlockFi is not responsible for any typos or mistakes made entering this information.</p></div></div></div></div><h3 id="faq-a-eligible">Who is eligible for the BlockFi Interest Account?</h3><div class="answer"><p>The BlockFi Interest Account is available to clients worldwide, with a few exceptions. For example, due to legal restrictions, BIA is not available to users located in sanctioned or watchlist countries. Additionally, the Interest Account services clients in most U.S. states, but is not available New York and Connecticut.</p><h3 id="faq-a-collateral">Can collateral posted for a loan be used to earn interest?</h3><div class="answer"><p>Collateral posted for a loan is not eligible for earning interest.</p><h3 id="faq-a-assets">What does BlockFi do with account assets?</h3><div class="answer"><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">BlockFi generates interest on assets held in Interest Accounts by lending them to trusted institutional and corporate borrowers. To ensure loan performance, BlockFi lends crypto on over-collateralized terms (similar to the structure of our crypto-backed loans). Furthermore, BlockFi’s automated risk management system monitors positions 24/7, providing the same trusted risk management system used with </span><a href="https://blockfi.com/get-crypto-backed-loan"><span style="font-weight: 400;">BlockFi’s crypto-backed loans</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. &nbsp;BlockFi has the ability to terminate a borrow in a timely fashion and also manages reserve balances to facilitate clients withdrawals from Interest Accounts. Reserves are stored securely with our primary custodian <a href="https://getstarted.gemini.com/gemini-blockfi/">Gemini</a>, a New York trust company regulated by NYDFS. Learn more about </span><a href="https://blockfi.com/securely-stored-assets"><span style="font-weight: 400;">how BlockFi stores clients assets</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p><h3 id="faq-a-tax">What are the tax implications of the BlockFi Interest Account?</h3><div class="answer"><p>US clients will receive a 1099 shortly after the end of the year which details the total dollar value of interest paid over the year. Clients can provide this information to their tax preparers who can advise based on individual facts and circumstances. International clients are responsible for determining their own tax obligations. BlockFi will provide international clients with a summary of their account activity upon request.</p><h3 id="faq-a-smart-contract">Can I send BlockFi ETH through a smart contract?</h3><div class="answer"><p>ETH sent to BlockFi through a smart contracts will show up on users dashboards, but there may be delays arising from special transaction requirements in the contract. For the fastest credit, we recommend sending ETH normally.</p><h3 id="faq-a-fees">Does the BlockFi Interest Account have withdrawal fees?</h3><div class="answer"><p>We offer one free withdrawal per client per month. After that, our primary custodian <a href="https://getstarted.gemini.com/gemini-blockfi/">Gemini</a> passes on a withdrawal fee of either 0.0025 BTC or 0.0015 ETH.</p><div id="faq-a-risks" class="row faq-item"><div id="contactinfo" class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"><div class="answer"><h3>What are the risks associated with a BlockFi Interest Account?</h3><div class="answer"><p>BlockFi client funds are structured to be at the top of the capital stack, senior to BlockFi equity and BlockFi employee capital. This means BlockFi’s business and client incentives are aligned and BlockFi would take a loss before any client would. BlockFi implements very thoughtful risk management practices and technology to mitigate the risk, but you should not view the BlockFi Interest Account as a savings account or brokerage account with FDIC or SIPC insurance.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><h2 id="heading-loan-structure">BlockFi Loan Structure</h2><div id="faq-a" class="row faq-item"><div id="contactinfo" class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"><h3>How did you determine the loan to value ratio?</h3><div class="answer"><p>We have performed extensive risk modeling and determined that our LTVs were sufficiently conservative — in order to have a limited number of expected trigger events and provide our clients with breathing room in the event of market volatility. The LTV ratios protect you and us.&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: 400;">Learn more about </span><a href="https://blockfi.com/bitcoin-loan-ltv-compared"><span style="font-weight: 400;">how LTVs work</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p></div></div></div><div id="faq-b" class="row faq-item"><div id="contactinfo" class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"><h3>Is there a prepayment penalty?</h3><div class="answer"><p>There is no penalty for early repayment, so if you payoff early the remaining interest is forgiven. Once your loan is paid off, collateral is released to your preferred address.&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: 400;">Learn more about </span><a href="https://blockfi.com/early-crypto-loan-repayment"><span style="font-weight: 400;">how prepayment works</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p></div></div></div><div id="faq-c" class="row faq-item"><div id="contactinfo" class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"><h3>What happens if the value of my cryptoassets significantly increase or decrease during the one year term?</h3><div class="answer"><p>If the value of your coins significantly increase then they are kept in storage until the loan is paid. If your coins significantly decrease then that sets off a trigger event, and you will have to add more collateral to your account to maintain a minimum LTV ratio. You can use the value of your cryptoassets stored with BlockFi to make principal and interest payments at anytime. We plan to add the ability to draw more USD funds in the event of price appreciation over time.&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: 400;">Learn more about </span><a href="https://blockfi.com/crypto-collateral-value"><span style="font-weight: 400;">what happens to your collateral with price fluctuations</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p></div></div></div><div id="faq-d" class="row faq-item"><div id="contactinfo" class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"><h3>What is a trigger event?</h3><div class="answer"><p>A trigger event happens when the value of your collateral drops and thus increases the LTV of your loan. The first trigger event occurs at a 70% LTV. At this point, you have 72 hours to take action by positing additional collateral or paying down the loan balance. We will keep you informed if your LTV starts to near the 70% mark so you can take action preemptively.</p></div></div></div><div id="faq-e" class="row faq-item"><div id="contactinfo" class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"><h3>How will I know if I am close to a trigger event?</h3><div class="answer no-border"><p>We will send you notification emails if your LTV is approaching 70%.</p></div></div></div><h2 id="heading-loan-process">Loan Process</h2><div id="faq-l" class="row faq-item"><div id="contactinfo" class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"><h3>How can I get a loan?</h3><div class="answer"><ol><li>Create an account at&nbsp;https://app.blockfi.com/signup</li><li>Click on the Loan tab</li><li>Click Apply and fill out the application.</li><li>You will receive a decision from our team in less than 24 hours</li><li>Review your loan offer and sign the loan agreement</li><li>Transfer collateral to BlockFi’s secure storage wallet</li><li>Receive your loan the same day in USD via a wire to your bank account or stablecoin to your wallet address of choice.</li><li>Make interest only payments monthly using USD, BTC, ETH or LTC</li><li>Pay off the principal in one payment at the end of the term or refinance at current rates</li></ol></div></div></div><div id="faq-m" class="row faq-item"><div id="contactinfo" class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"><h3>Will my credit score be affected by applying for a BlockFi loan?</h3><div class="answer"><p>No, BlockFi does not do a hard or soft pull on your credit score so there is no impact for applying. Learn more about <a href="https://blockfi.com/crypto-loan-credit-score">how BlockFi affects client credit scores</a>.</p></div></div></div><div id="faq-n" class="row faq-item"><div id="contactinfo" class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"><h3>Where can I login to view my loan details?</h3><div class="answer no-border"><p>Your loan details are viewable from within our client portal. Login to your account at https://app.blockfi.com/signin. Additional information can be viewed at our loan servicer, who will reach out to you via email post-funding to set up an account. You will be able to view your loan details, collateral amount, and set up auto-pay.</p></div></div></div><h2 id="heading-rates">Rates</h2><div id="faq-f" class="row faq-item"><div id="contactinfo" class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"><h3>What is the interest rate?</h3><div class="answer no-border"><p>We’re a bit different from typical consumer lenders in that our underwriting and interest rates are based on the collateral instead of your quality as a borrower. For example, we don’t take personal credit scores into account. BlockFi’s interest rates vary based on a number of variables, including location, loan size, collateral type, and LTV. Check out <a href="https://blockfi.com/">home page</a> to see our most up to date interest rates.</p></div></div></div><h2 id="heading-security-storage">Security or Collateral Storage</h2><div id="faq-g" class="row faq-item"><div id="contactinfo" class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"><h3>Where are my cryptoassets stored?</h3><div class="answer no-border"><p>Your cryptoassets are deposited into an account with <a href="https://getstarted.gemini.com/gemini-blockfi/">Gemini</a>, our primary custodian and a licensed depository trust. Detailed information on Gemini’s security program and digital asset insurance can be found <a href="https://gemini.com/security/">here</a> and <a href="https://gemini.com/user-agreement/#digital-asset-insurance">here</a>. The majority of assets stored with Gemini are held in cold storage. Read more about <a href="https://blockfi.com/securely-stored-assets">how BlockFi stores client funds</a>.</p></div></div></div><h2 id="heading-general">General</h2><div id="faq-h" class="row faq-item"><div id="contactinfo" class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"><h3>What is BlockFi?</h3><div class="answer"><p>BlockFi offers financial products designed to help cryptocurrency holders to do more with their digital assets. The company currently services clients worldwide, including 48 U.S. states, with interest earning accounts and low cost USD loans backed by crypto. BlockFi is the only independent lender with institutional backing from investors that include Galaxy Digital, Susquehanna, Akuna Capital, Fidelity, Recruit Strategic Partners, ConsenSys Ventures, SoFi, Coinbase Ventures, CMT Digital and Morgan Creek Digital.</p></div></div></div><div id="faq-i" class="row faq-item"><div id="contactinfo" class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"><h3>What are the benefits of using BlockFi’s services?</h3><div class="answer"><p>BlockFi offers institutional-quality financial services to crypto investors. Everything from our client services to our products are based on tried and tested policies to provide a superior experience for our clients.</p><p>The BlockFi Interest Account provides clients with the ability to earn more crypto while holding for long-term investments. Interest is paid monthly and compounds. This significantly increases the potential earnings of long-term account holders.</p><p>A loan from BlockFi enables you to use your cryptoassets as collateral and receive USD to your bank account. Borrowing against your cryptoassets enables you to receive liquidity now but does not trigger a capital gains tax event and, depending on the use of funds, the interest may be deductible against capital gains and other investment income.</p><p>BlockFi does not provide financial or tax advice and you should consider your financial situation and seek appropriate financial and tax advice before deciding to use our services.</p></div></div></div><div id="faq-j" class="row faq-item"><div id="contactinfo" class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"><h3>Why BlockFi?</h3><div class="answer"><p>We offer the best rates, most flexible structures and highest degree of security available in the blockchain lending ecosystem. Additionally, we operate within regulatory guidelines at the federal and state level in the United States.</p><p>The BlockFi <a href="https://blockfi.com/team/">team</a> has decades of experience in consumer lending and financial services. We are<span style="font-weight: 400;">&nbsp;the only independent lender with institutional backing from investors that include Galaxy Digital, Susquehanna, Akuna Capital, Fidelity, Recruit Strategic Partners, ConsenSys Ventures, SoFi, Coinbase Ventures, CMT Digital and Morgan Creek Digital. <a href="https://blockfi.com/investors/">Learn more about our investors</a>.</span></p></div></div></div><div id="faq-k" class="row faq-item"><div id="contactinfo" class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"><h3>Who can use the product?</h3><div class="answer no-border"><p>BlockFi services individuals and businesses worldwide, including 47 U.S. states, which is the largest footprint in the industry.</p><h3>How does the refer a friend program work?</h3><div class="answer no-border"><p>When users login to BlockFi, the dashboard will display a Refer a Friend button at the top right corner of the page. When clicked, a pop-up will display the user’s unique code that can be shared on any site and used to refer new clients to BlockFi. Anyone who creates an account in the session following a click on that URL will be tagged to your account. If the new user funds their account, you will receive a referral award for getting them to join BlockFi. If the new user funds a BIA, you will earn 10% of the interest generated from their funded account, funded directly into your BIA at the beginning of every month. This will continue for the lifetime of the account, as long as that client maintains a balance in their BlockFi Interest Account (BIA). If the new user takes out a loan, you will receive $50 or 10 basis points of the loan amount (whichever number is greater).</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid vc_custom_1545935164337 full-width-section " style="margin-left: -467.5px; padding-left: 467.5px; padding-right: 467.5px; visibility: visible; width: 100%; margin-right: 0px;"><div class="vc_span12 wpb_column vc_column_container "><div class="vc_column-inner "><div class="wpb_wrapper"><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_inner vc_row-fluid vc_custom_1545232608842"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_sp